CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 27, 1974, pg. 26, reads: "Between Raindrops - Easter Sunday showers did not dampen the spirits of these two young Homewood lads, Eugene Anderson and Gregory Bandy.  Borrowing the protection of the bombershoot, topcoat and baseball jacket, they sported their bright plaid and checks and gay floral prints, coordinating colors with big head-gear. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Eugene Anderson wearing plaid coat, and Gregory Bandy holding umbrella and walking on sidewalk, possibly Homewood
